(9, 'Festival Sunday: Sunday 12 February', 'Nicolas Hanson', 'Mr. Calamaro', 'Po Box 777', 'Frankston', 'Victoria', '3199', 'nico05@optusnet.com.au', 'nico05@optusnet.com.au', '0478568173', '', 'Mr. Calamaro\nFine fryer guys.\n\nFryer guy\nService guy\nService girl\n\nMr. Calamaros story. \nFather and son operation with a common happiness and excitement for food and family.\n\nMr. Calamaros ethos.\nWorking hard to create a sustainable operation. Thinking about our planet and the impact when we consume food.\n\nMr. calamaros make up.\nHand-cut calamari \nLocally grown and sourced lemons & snow pea shoots \nBiodegradable packaging\nRecycled & Refined oil  \nAustralian designed and manufactured Deep Fryer. \nHomemade aiolis\n\nMr. Calamaro\nFine fryers guys.\n\nMenu \n\nFries ($6.00)\nGippsland Potatoes\nFresh picked lemon wedge\n\n\nBocadillo-Calamari in a roll ($8.50)\nHand-cut Calamari\nBasque guindilla pepper\nParsely\nHomemade aioli\nFresh picked lemon wedge\nLocally baked fresh bocadillo (roll)\n\n\nCalamari in a boat ($12.00)\nHand-cut Calamari\nServed with fresh snow pea shoots\nBasque guindilla pepper\nHomemade aioli\nFresh picked lemon wedge\n\n\n', 'Yes', '2012-08-14 06:10:21'),
